rComments: This was a seminar course but often didn't give much chance for student participation, would ask a question someone would answer and then he would give a mini lecture and then move on to another topic without giving much of a chance for anyone else to participate, readings every week were very long often entire books.

It takes legitimate talent to be this poor as a prof. He speaks in circles, he describes people and events in Medieval history as if you know them completely, which is rather silly, given that this is an intro course, and he doesn't answer questions well. No textbook either. Where we're supposed to learn ABOUT these things. Incredibly bad. Run.
he is a very nice, however difficult to follow.
Professor was enthusiastic , but it was incredibly difficult to follow in class due to a tremendous amount of course material.

I took this as a half course, so hopefully it will be a full year again. There is way too much information to be learned. This is a note-heavy class, since there is no textbook. The marking is very fair.
The WORST teacher I have ever had.
